[size=5][b]Graveyard Keeper — Multiplayer (2-player co-op)[/b][/size]

Adds [b]2-player co-op[/b] to Graveyard Keeper. Connection is over Steam P2P — no server to set up, no port forwarding, no IP addresses. One of you hosts, the other joins through a regular Steam invite.

[b]Status:[/b] beta. The core loop is fully playable together: world, building, crafting, graves, inventory. NPC villagers and dungeon mobs are not synced yet (see Known limitations).

[size=4][b]What is synced[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Both players in the same world — the host's save is transferred automatically on join
[*]Movement, animations, day/night time (anyone sleeping advances time for both)
[*]Tree chopping, stone breaking, mining loot, foraging, garden beds
[*][b]Graves[/b] — digging, reburying bodies, repair; carried corpses with handoff between players
[*][b]Building[/b] — full cycle: place → construct → demolish
[*][b]Crafting at workstations[/b] — shared queues, live progress bar on your partner's side
[*][b]Inventory[/b] — shared chests (both can use them at once), stockpiles, item exchange
[*]Weather, shared story world-flags
[*][b]Personal progress[/b] — the 2nd player has their own character save (skills, HP, techs, perks, quest journal) layered over the host's world. Shared world, personal progress — the Stardew Valley model
[/list]

[size=4][b]Installation (step by step)[/b][/size]

[b]Step 1 — Install BepInEx (the mod loader):[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Download [b]BepInEx 5.4.23.5 (x64)[/b] — the file is [i]BepInEx_x64_5.4.23.5.zip[/i] from the [url=https://github.com/BepInEx/BepInEx/releases/tag/v5.4.23.5]BepInEx releases page[/url]
[*]Extract it [b]directly into the game folder[/b] — the one with [i]Graveyard Keeper.exe[/i] (usually [i]C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Graveyard Keeper[/i]). After extracting you should see a [i]BepInEx[/i] folder and [i]winhttp.dll[/i] next to the game's exe
[*][b]Launch the game once and quit[/b] — this makes BepInEx generate its folders (including [i]BepInEx\plugins[/i])
[/list]

[b]Step 2 — Install the mod:[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Drop [i]Multiplayer.dll[/i] (from the Files tab) into [i]Graveyard Keeper\BepInEx\plugins\[/i]
[/list]

[b]Both[/b] players do steps 1–2, with the [b]same version[/b] of the mod. Launch the game [b]through Steam[/b] — otherwise Steamworks won't initialize.

[size=4][b]How to play[/b][/size]

[b]Host:[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Load your save
[*]Press [b]F11[/b] — a lobby is created and the Steam invite overlay opens
[*]Invite your friend
[/list]

[b]Client:[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Accept the Steam invite
[*]The mod downloads the host's save and joins you into the world
[/list]

Game progress doesn't matter — you can invite from day 1. In a brand-new game, press F11 right after the interface appears (early on, at the graveyard).

[size=4][b]F11 seems to do nothing?[/b][/size]

The lobby [b]is[/b] created — the invite window is drawn by the [b]Steam Overlay[/b], so if the overlay is disabled you won't see anything. Two ways out:
[list]
[*]Enable the overlay: Steam → Settings → In Game → [i]Enable the Steam overlay while in-game[/i] (also check the game's Properties)
[*]Or skip it: press F11 anyway, then your friend joins via the Steam friends list — right-click your name → [b]Join Game[/b]. Works even with the overlay off on both sides
[/list]

[size=4][b]Known limitations[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]2 players max (for now)
[*]NPC villagers and dungeon mobs/zombies are not synced yet — you'll each see your own
[*]Both players need the game on Steam (P2P runs through Steam networking)
[*]DLC: a player without the DLCs can join and play fine, [b]until[/b] the host starts a paid DLC storyline — then the save won't load for them
[/list]

[size=4][b]Bug reports[/b][/size]

Bug reports are the most useful thing you can give this mod right now. If something breaks, post what happened, and if possible: set [i]DebugMode = true[/i] in [i]BepInEx\config\com.denys.multiplayer.cfg[/i] and attach [i]BepInEx\LogOutput.log[/i] from both players. Logs contain no personal data beyond Steam display names.

[size=4][b]Support[/b][/size]

This mod is free and always will be. If you'd like to support development: [url=https://ko-fi.com/zonda]ko-fi.com/zonda[/url]. Totally optional — bug reports and testing help just as much. ❤

